00:18:56,710 --> 00:18:59,910
[Yao State's Imperial Palace]

363
00:18:57,920 --> 00:19:00,000
By decree of His Majesty

364
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:02,790
and the Empress Dowager,

365
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:04,680
Shi Du is hereby promoted

366
00:19:04,680 --> 00:19:06,640
to General of the Cavalry,

367
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:07,960
and Zhao Jingyuan

368
00:19:07,960 --> 00:19:09,960
to General of the Chariots.

369
00:19:10,110 --> 00:19:11,200
Furthermore,

370
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:12,920
General Shi Du

371
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:15,480
is appointed to guard the Southern Pass.

372
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:25,110
Thank you, Your Majesties!

373
00:19:29,270 --> 00:19:30,590
Your Majesties,

374
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:32,880
the General of the Cavalry
and the General of the Chariots

375
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:34,620
are crucial military positions.

376
00:19:34,620 --> 00:19:35,930
Shi Du and Zhao Jingyuan

377
00:19:35,930 --> 00:19:37,160
are still too inexperienced.

378
00:19:37,160 --> 00:19:38,790
I'm afraid they are not suited
for these positions.

379
00:19:38,790 --> 00:19:39,440
I implore

380
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:41,170
Your Majesties to reconsider.

381
00:19:44,830 --> 00:19:45,920
I'm not suited?

382
00:19:46,240 --> 00:19:48,700
Is Prime Minister Zuo,
at this advanced age,

383
00:19:49,110 --> 00:19:51,770
going to go to the front lines
and face the enemy?

384
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:53,640
After the Battle of Lucheng,

385
00:19:53,640 --> 00:19:55,070
our army was severely weakened.

386
00:19:55,070 --> 00:19:56,220
If Prince Annan were here,

387
00:19:56,220 --> 00:19:58,550
he would likely advise rest and recovery.

388
00:19:58,580 --> 00:19:59,830
Sending out troops rashly

389
00:19:59,830 --> 00:20:01,030
would not be a wise decision.

390
00:20:01,030 --> 00:20:03,090
I urge Your Majesties to reconsider.

391
00:20:03,790 --> 00:20:05,190
In the Battle of Lucheng,

392
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,350
Duan Aodeng left his post
without permission,

393
00:20:07,350 --> 00:20:08,350
causing our army

394
00:20:08,350 --> 00:20:09,680
to be utterly defeated.

395
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:12,000
Her Majesty considered
he was the late emperor's brother,

396
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,680
so she chose not
to hold him accountable for the defeat,

397
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:15,240
and ordered a grand funeral for him.

398
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:16,480
Yet, Prime Minister Zuo

399
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:18,510
keeps mentioning Prince Annan.

400
00:20:18,920 --> 00:20:20,270
Are you suggesting that without him,

401
00:20:20,270 --> 00:20:22,550
our Yao State has no capable men left?

402
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:24,480
Prince Annan
spent his life on the battlefield,

403
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:26,160
and devoted his whole life to our state!

404
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:28,110
How dare you belittle him?

405
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:33,880
However,

406
00:20:34,350 --> 00:20:36,080
I would like to ask Her Majesty.

407
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:38,160
Although Prince Annan was buried,

408
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:39,520
the body

409
00:20:39,790 --> 00:20:40,680
in the coffin

410
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:42,070
was unrecognizable.

411
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:43,440
Furthermore,

412
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:44,640
all Prince Annan's guards

413
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:47,000
were slaughtered overnight.

414
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:47,960
I'm afraid

415
00:20:48,160 --> 00:20:50,350
someone's plotting behind the scenes.

416
00:20:50,350 --> 00:20:51,750
There must be more

417
00:20:52,070 --> 00:20:53,240
to Prince Annan's death.

418
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:54,770
How dare you, Zuo Chengzhi!

419
00:20:54,830 --> 00:20:57,070
Are you saying someone
deliberately swapped the body

420
00:20:57,070 --> 00:20:58,750
and hid Prince Annan?

421
00:20:59,030 --> 00:21:00,880
That's absurd!

422
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:05,920
The late Emperor was assassinated,

423
00:21:05,920 --> 00:21:07,920
and Prince Annan went with him.

424
00:21:08,110 --> 00:21:09,440
No citizen of Yao State

425
00:21:09,510 --> 00:21:12,170
can tolerate such
a national and personal debt.

426
00:21:13,070 --> 00:21:13,920
We must

427
00:21:14,550 --> 00:21:15,680
fight this war!

428
00:21:17,550 --> 00:21:19,270
As for the burial,

429
00:21:19,640 --> 00:21:21,030
the late Emperor and Prince Annan

430
00:21:21,030 --> 00:21:22,880
were brave men of Yao State.

431
00:21:23,070 --> 00:21:24,720
As a woman,

432
00:21:25,440 --> 00:21:26,550
I could only do my best

433
00:21:26,550 --> 00:21:29,130
to give them a dignified farewell.

434
00:21:29,510 --> 00:21:31,230
Mr. Zuo, if you have doubts,

435
00:21:31,510 --> 00:21:33,310
you are welcome to investigate yourself.

436
00:21:33,310 --> 00:21:34,960
I will absolutely not

437
00:21:35,310 --> 00:21:36,920
raise any objection.

438
00:21:38,110 --> 00:21:39,030
Prince Annan

439
00:21:39,030 --> 00:21:40,550
was our greatest general,

440
00:21:40,660 --> 00:21:42,860
and the current Emperor's uncle.

441
00:21:43,270 --> 00:21:44,480
Whether he lives or not

442
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:45,790
is of great significance.

443
00:21:45,790 --> 00:21:46,440
I request

444
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:48,040
Your Majesties' permission

445
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:49,030
to send out

446
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:51,510
search parties,

447
00:21:51,510 --> 00:21:53,830
leave no clue unchecked,

448
00:21:54,750 --> 00:21:56,080
and put Your Majesties'

449
00:21:56,270 --> 00:21:57,200
minds at ease.

450
00:21:58,270 --> 00:22:00,640
Such loyalty from Minister Zuo

451
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:02,650
is truly Yao State's blessing.

452
00:22:04,070 --> 00:22:06,160
Then let's do as
Prime Minister Zuo suggests.

453
00:22:06,160 --> 00:22:08,480
Your Majesty is truly wise.

454
